   described and illustrated from Mangkang county, Tibet, China. F.
   homotropicum was firstly discovered in the 90's, being to be diploid and
   characterized being a self-pollinating taxon. Detailed information of F.
   homotropiucm was rarely reported. In this paper, we summarized the
   morphological and karyological characters of tetraploid form F.
   homotropiucm (2n=4x=32), it is self-pollinating, and morphology
